			<div class="content" id="post-content-1541058">
									

<p>Adding the fourth log would just ruin it. The author has built a beautiful set-up of suspense and horror that would fall apart if everything was revealed. Your burning desire to see what happened during the fourth expedition? Your frustration with the mystery? That's what the author <em>wants</em> you to feel. After all, fear of the unknown is the greatest fear of all.</p>
<p>This article has been around for a while, anyway. There's really nothing that could possibly live up to the mystery.</p>
<p>Interesting interpretation, though.</p>

